    </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1164846554387">The fourth  figure in Figure 4  is for  T &lt;&lt; τ. In this case we get the mean value only. The square wave is lost.So at very high frequencies, LPF acts as INTEGRATOR.</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1164847714479">The frequency domain analysis is given below with reference to Figure 3:<emphasis effect="bold"/></para>
    <figure id="import-auto-id1164847813912">
      <media id="import-auto-id1164846601367" alt="">
        <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics14-3fb5.png" height="56" width="479"/>
